reviews.text: Hipster district!
Beautiful!
Hay un lugar para orientar a los turistas
Es sobre todo un lugar pintoresco, construcción antigua muy bien cuidada.

Se ofrecen servicios culturales pero creo que para ser un distrito tan emblemático como Barranco que muy por debajo de los demás lugares turísticos y culturales.
Queda como un bonito edificio

super fair! beautiful. they have great coffee, good avocado ice cream, good little places to snack or pick on something, bags, purses, clothes and natural beauty products. they have different things that are strange to find. good prices!
That's a nice place to be happy. It has a very enjoyable environment and you can also have a nice time listening live music.
We randomly walked into this place one evening when we visited Lima. Picked up some unique art pieces here and the band was really good the night we visited.

Cute outdoor market of local artesans ... You won't find Peru souvenirs, but you will find Made in Peru beach cover-ups and dresses and purses, and local perfumes etc. Back section has activities for pups and kiddos
Great outdoor marker that offers food, clothing from independent designers and other fun knickknacks. There is often a band playing too!

This is a small, well kept museum with the story of electrical generation, substation equipment, transformers and other electric devices.  Free entry, offering wonderful exhibits of restored equipment and a variety of electric appliances including ham radios, two "Wurlitzer Rocolas" and an operating trolley.  It is a great place for kids and the trolley ride is fun.  The trolley rails need to be repaired and Barranco should seriously get a fund raiser to fix them.  Also, people who live along the track right-of-way should have the common sense not to park on the tracks.  It ruins the ride for everyone.
It's a very interesting little museum and entrance is free.
Free and fun quick stop. Had small activities built into the learning which makes it fun to walk around.
Great
I don't think it's that impressive a museum to visit.  Very small and not-so-great exhibitions, sadly.
Great food, their ceviche is must try! Fantastic views and can hear the waves and feel an ocean breeze. Good service.
The view is great, food is so so. Terrible smell inside the restaurant not possible to seat down. Service is slow.

We went here during our short visit in Lima. We had one night and came here as a recommendation from our hotel.  The restaurant was beautiful.  We sat outside overlooking the beautiful ocean. We specifically came here for ceviche... which was delicious. However, the service was not great. We felt forgotten.  Once seated, we sat for 15 min before anyone even gave us menus. Once we had the menus,  it was another 15-20 min to order. The two items we wanted to order,  they were out of.  So, we both ordered something else and was not impressed. Our driver had actually recommended the restaurant right down the street and I think we should of taken his advice.

This was one of my favorite in Lima! Looooved the green ceviche (cilantro) and I can’t wait to taste it again. I went in 2016 btw. 

All the dishes were amazing! The place was a bit packed and it’s A bit too expensive but worth. We didn’t get a table with view, wish we had!
Beautiful and romantic location. Delicious food
Fantastic live criolla music, great dancing, warm, friendly environment, good food and drink.  Make a reservation! It is small and gets packed!
Fun ,safe, cheap, good.

If you are fan of Creole Music this is the place for you, otherwise skipping might be a good idea. The atmosphere is autentic, the music is live. Most of the visitors are middle aged (and a bit more) locals. The musicians are really good - playing hard guitar progressions - but the lack of rhythm in this music might be pretty hard to understand/enjoy to anyone who doesn't have it in his blood.

Nice spot to listen to some good oldies and enjoy the dance floor. 

The $25sol cover covers a free drink. The food here is wonderful. But definitely come here for the music. Staff only speaks Spanish, but are patient enough to describe the food and service. 

Note: Make a reservation before arriving or you will be suck in the corner. Really really small restroom.
Best live show. Time travel

For the price, you could eat at a nice restaurant and get much better quality of food. Food isn’t terrible but it ain’t worth it. The restaurant it self as a stablishment is very nice, and they dancing shows portraying typical dances, that’s why they got the 2nd star. But again... I think you could get more for your buck somewhere else. Hopefully they can revisit their recipes, some are bland, other too salty, others didn’t seem to offer good quality of products.
The menu ms terrible compared to what you can find in ANY restaurant here in Peru. And the price os completely exagerated

Every dish is good to very good. You can get slightly better if any dish at a restaurant that specialises but here you can try everything. Highly recommend early in your trip to check all the boxes and then enjoy exploring the cuisine of Peru. Only dish not here is cuy.

Parking is a little troublesome, but the person attending the valet parking is always doing more than he suppose to do to help the people with their cars.
Food is ok (buffet) but the quality of each dish is nothing comparable to others restaurant dedicated to one type of dish. Which is also something good about this place, you can eat every type of Peruvian food in one place, with not the best but some good quality and variety.
Only thing I would not recommend is the Japanese rolls or makis, the rice was raw, and the preparation of the Maki was the worst I have ever tasted. Table attention for drinks is ok.
A bit pricey; it’s not special and doesn’t worth 100 soles.
Great food, excellent customer service and delivered main dishes pretty fast. Recommended no doubts.

Oh WOW!!! The owner is AMAZING, the food oh the food, THE FOOD, tender meat, everything is cooked perfectly. The service is GREAT you don't have to wait a long time for anything. I'll rep this place everyday ALL day. It's just incredible! More than recommended don't come to Heredia and miss out on La Candelaria anything you eat there is/will be GREAT guaranteed. Just an explosion of flavors!!!
Nice place, good price, goos service
Great food, great location, good pricing.. but most important.. they're pet friendly 🐾🐾  one of the best places to go with my dogs.
Somewhat pricey but worth it. Great place to meet and enjoy coffee at a pleasant place.

This is an amazing place to visit. NOT suitable for handicap people.One of the oldest churches and convent since Spanish Colonial times.The gold covered altars, the paintings and the tour to the catacombs make this an interesting place to visit.The entry ticket was very reasonable.You need to go in a tour.Too many steps for people with troubled knees.No availability for wheel chairs.It is better to go on weekends.
Very neat place if you are in to history. Alot of great architecture and art work. The catacombs were really cool to see. Worth a visit of you have a few days in Lima.

An amazing visit. The inside is wonderful. Very vibrant area with many wonderful shops restuarants terrific bars. Visit the square just down the road and he old railway station on the way and the bar on the corner and the chocolate shop.

What a beautiful little courtyard lined with gorgeous architecture and charming atmosphere. It's like walking onto the set of a classic movie with street peddlers and pigeons everywhere.  I wish I had known about the catacombs when we were there, we actually stumbled upon it by accident.

Amazing sights and history. If you want to visit the catacombs, you must take part in the guided tour, English speaking ones are every half hour on weekends. The only downside is that you are not allowed to take pictures of anything in the church, monastery or catacombs even with a cellphone without flash.

The Convento de Santa Clara is a large and interesting convent to explore with beautiful gardens, a gorgeous courtyard, and detailed colonial architecture. It was great for photography! 

Inside the tall walls surrounding this convent, I discovered such beautiful and intricate colonial architecture, a pretty water fountain in the centre of an amazing courtyard, expansive rooms and gorgeous manicured gardens. The courtyard was surrounded by buildings with beautiful arches. There were lots of pathways, hallways and interesting hidden areas to explore and it was a really beautiful place to wander around. 

The views of the courtyard and volcano landscape were amazing after climbing the stairs to the top of the ruins. 

This convent was a fascinating place to explore and take photos and the atmosphere was so peaceful and relaxed. The entrance fee was Q40. This convent is definitely worth a visit when in Antigua! Review based on my experience visiting in November 2016.
Nice colonial style convent
Nice 👍
Really worth the time to stop by here and get a feel for the scale of this convent.
I guess this is the most beautiful convent in this city. Very peaceful and "señorial"

Es un museo pequeño pero tiene características interesantes para el que quiere saber sobre las comunidades nativas. Están enfocados en los de la zona Sur del país. 
Muy luminoso, gráfico e inclusive tienen una biblioteca para los que les interese leer un poco más sobre estas comunidades.
Personalmente me encantó!

Es un museo perteneciente a la PUCP. Es agradable para visitar o pasear.
Interesante muestra del Perú milenario

Pequeño museo de piezas arqueológicas perteneciente a la Pontificia universidad católica del Perú ubicado en la Plaza Francia en el Centro de Lima.
Es un pequeño museo que complementa lo que puede ser una breve visita o paseo por la Plaza Francia y la iglesia de la Recoleta.
El lugar es un edificio relativamente moderno y tiene ascensor para poder acceder a los pisos superiores.
Los vigilantes son amables y pueden dar información sobre la exposición.
Es importante leer toda la información, Lima es también ciudad Arqueológica, Lima,  el Perú tenenos mucha historia.
Lugar excelente para entender la lima prehispánica
Beaitiful colonial mansion.
Oloroso

La Universidad ofrece muchos programas de apoyo estudiantil especialmente para impulsar proyectos. Es una pena que han habido muchos reclamos porque los pagos son altos, y no actúan con valores católicos sino como empresa a la hora de cobrar. En general, hay una buena educación.
Muy bien conservado
El Instituto Riva-Agüero de la PUCP ofrece diversos cursos y conferencias. Además de contar con un museo y biblioteca.

Excellent museum! Lots of rich history here presented very elegantly. Great for an afternoon. Wonderful glimpse of the many civilizations of Peru. Do plan to stay for a meal at the restaurant, which is quite romantic. They were able to accommodate an oil-free, gluten-free, vegan diet, which was super appreciated. They customized the solterito this way for us and it was delicious.

Lovely building in a beautiful setting. It has many ancient artifacts from centuries of Peruvian culture. It is very easy to get around and feels more intimate than many large museums. The gardens surrounding the building are very lush and well kept.

A beautiful, nicely laid out and reasonably priced museum, with amazingly well-preserved exhibits.

There's an intro video in four languages (two versions, each with a different spoken [English & Spanish] and subtitled[German & French] language), and then you're off on your own or with a guide.

The exhibits themselves are very well preserved and/or restored, and there's plaques in several languages (English, Spanish, German, French, and.. Chinese, I think?)

The only caveat is that, if you're of a prurient bent, the pottery is sometimes suggestive (especially in the "erotic pottery" building and the gift shop).  That said, I recommend you keep an open mind - it's not smut, it's simply a part of the cultures that are exhibited.

(cost was $9USD for the museum ticket, and the guide was about $3 more)

This a unique place. Came a cross one day on my trip to Peru. Not busy and they offer guided tour for cheap. A lot of good history the jars and other sexual sculptures are in a different section that's good in case you are with your kids. Nothing gross or offensive but some parents would not like to expose the young ones to this kinda thing. Beautiful place overall. I believe there is restaurant in here too

Incredible place, gorgeous gardens and flowers around. The exhibition is outstanding, we had a tour and our guide was very passionate about Peruvian heritage. Highly recommended to visit if you in Lima.
Very very good on the park
A quiet place to read and chat
Good park during the day, there are many seats and open space to rest and walk, but at night it is quite dark because of the lights that are no properly maintained.
ok

This is a beautiful park in the middle of Lima's centre. It's like an oasis in the desert. The views of the city are awesome, also you can find the Italian art museum close to this park.
A must visit in Lima.
It's a beautiful place but as many places that are located in downtown Lima, you have to be careful of your belongings, good place to take pictures and rest for awhile if you are walking nearby.

Public space located in Abancay avenue in Lima Downtown. There are stray cats everywhere. Very nice place at day, but at night, it's not recommended to stop by because it's dangerous, more if you're tourist.
Nice place. Recommended for turist during day time only. Not at night!
Quiet than in the past. Well maintained and some Serenazgo guys working for your security. It would be better if the huge clock is repaired.
This park is not a tourist magnet, full of locals. Quite dirty, but there always seems to be something lively going on here.
A small but nice place.
Muy linda, falta que la iluminacion se encienda en la noche.... esta, pero apagada
Uma praça encantadora, com muitos restaurantes e lojas que remetem ao período vintage.
科洛尼亞老城最中心的廣場，週邊是各種歷史古蹟，遊客雲集。
Ciudad vieja en reconstrucción.
A beautiful Square.  when u drive you can see it
Is nice to watch it but I don't recommend to stay. Dangerous at night.
The architecture is unbelievable, beautiful, the vibrant, definitely coming more than once. The culture is unique !

This famous square was built in honor of the Peruvian hero General Francisco Bolognesi Cervantes, son of Italian emigrant, was a soldier who gave his life in the Battle of Arica during the Pacific War between Peru and Chile from 1879 to 1883.
Every 6th of June the Flag Day is celebrated in honor of his immolation.
From Plaza Bolognesi begins  Brasil Avenue towards west side of Lima, Alfonso Ugarte Ave to the east, Arica Ave to the northwest and on the other side to the beautiful Paseo Colon, where the Art Museum of Lima is and is adorned with statues of marble.
I forgot to note that the famous Salesian Catholic school is only two blocks away with its beautiful Basilica of Mary Help of Christians.
A beautiful place...
What a beautiful park. We went by it in a taxi a bit too fast but it's small and so pretty.
Very clean and open area.  Looks relatively safe to walk around.   There is a pizza hut in one of the corners and non registered vegetarian restaurants nearby.
Read up on the development of the square from a train yard to get insight into it's design.
This is the place where most, if not all, protest marches begin and/or end. During the day it's a nice place to visit, at night a visitor should be careful.

A magnificent plaza that co-joins different eras of architecture and the city's history. It's not only beautiful, but also remains one of Lima's most popular gathering spot. You can beat this place if you're into people watching!

Great place in Lima to explore japanese culture. Here you will find courses. They've got a place where you can read books, magazines, newspaper, mangas sitting on comfortable couchs. You may wanna attend their free events by looking the agenda on their website.

Very nice museum and cultural place.

Friendly staff and beautiful garden. 

It's a must see if you are interested in arts, culture and history.

The best place to learn about Japanese culture and enjoy the numerous presentations, expositions and performance they give along the year.

Fine place for eating and learning.
May be packed for certain events.
You can eat here. In two places. Enter first you have a restaurant but more inside too the left is a better place
Promo 2010
Cole

Un Colegio Parroquial Mixto primaria y Secundaria. Con Una formación Integral . Con talleres Deportivos por la tarde, bastante grande y Completo. Cursos de Fulbito, Voley ,Natación, Básquet, pongo pong,etc.
Es un lindo colegio y es muy completo, cuenta con Parroquia, coliseo y auditorio propio... Muy buena estructura!
Mi padre me comentó antes de morir que cuando niño, mientras era estudiante allí, un sacerdote abusó de él.

This place is very good they have great pizzas and offer a good array of pastas, sauces and salads. Theyalso offer dishes with fresh pasta. The ambient is nice and cozy giving it a homey feel in the first ambient while the second one has more space and big tables for going large groups for birthdays or other celebrations.
Best foood ever ...... the osobuco....wow !!! Like butter ...!

Nice place eat traditional pasta with different meats as saltimbocca and scallopines... The place is not as good as the meat but it is clean and with good service... You can bring your own wine without any extra charge for it... You can try the pasta alone or accompany with the meat of your preference...
Awesome Pizza; I definitely recommend and rate it!!!!
there was a hair in my food and the maneger insisted it was my own i have dined in the most expencive reasraunts all over the world and i have never experienced such bad customer service.
Huge portions, tasty food
Ok
Great food with local taste. Chaufa Pescado and Chupe de Camerones
Ok

Great restaurant & excellent service. My wife & I are from the US & found this restaurant online.  Neither did the food nor the excellent customer service disappoint us!
Every dish we tasted was delicious!!! Highly recommend even the desserts!
A must for Peruvian Northern cuisine. Nice cozy ambience, good service. Do notiss this place!

Very tastey sea food. 
But, when I first arrived three men came to the door step, including the owner and asked me what I want. I had to explain to them what kind of food I wanted before they let me in.

Cosy place with northern food,i like the attention of the friendly staff and so delicious the food  about fish you can quickly access to this place, also you can bring your friends for disgusting a delicious northern food. They accept all the card, they does not have private parking so that is disappointing but the location of this place is good
Ok
Buena atención. Cerca al centro histórico. Precio de la comida muy accesible y de gran tamaño. Se puede pedir para llevar.

La verdad q en el Rokys q esta al frente de la Plaza de Armas de Lima. Me gustó mucho su pollo, es jugoso. No había tenido buena experiencia con otros locales, pero este si lo recomendaría. Lo que si le falta es ventilación, ya que es muy cerrado y no tiene suficientes ventiladores.

Uno de los más restaurantes rokys del área, son una cadena de restaurantes que sirven pollo asado, son buenos y tienen buen gusto el. Precio es normal, aunque hay sitios más económicos, puedes comer tranquilamente en familia los precios de los platos. Oscilan entre los S/ 14 en adelante. Su comida es rica.
Un buen lugar para ir a comer porque cuenta con una carta variada, pero el lugar es algo pequeño.
Amusing Park. Well taken care of, I enjoyed it pretty much.

I think the other zoo in Lima is better. This zoo is not as well kept. Much of the windows for viewing animals were dirty on my visit. Some of the animals didn't seem very healthy. 
Their aquarium is very good. Lots of well known fish and is very well layed out
Compared to the other zoo in Lima this is much better. Seems better kept.

To spend a real quality time, to have some fun and also for learn about the animals. Spaces are well conserved, animals looks in very well conditions and spaces according to his needs. This is recomendable to visit when there is no so much people, for example the Monday to thrusday. There is parking at the entrance, bring a hat and repelend for mosquitos. Don't feed the animals they have well balanced food according to his needs. Inside there is a couple of restaurants no so expensive and aceptable quality. Some. Souvenirs of good quality are availables around the park topically animal shaped toys and so on. Bring your snickers and spend the whole day.
Animals are well kept. A good place to take the kids for a full day
Love the place. Amazing people always willing to help.
A beautiful place with a great show and even better food... The horses were magnificent!!!
Nice place to eat and relax watching 'caballos de paso' show...
Very beautiful place, great food and staff very welcoming.

The horses are quite handsome and their gait is natural not learned. The combination of dancing and synchronized movements of the horses make for an interesting show well worth seeing. The food was very good and the atmosphere very relaxing. Everyone was very nice and you could tell how much they loved their jobs and the animals.
Excellent food, excellent service. You will not be disappointed.
too expensive and bad food
Buemazoooo
Highly recommended seafood restaurant. Excellent ceviche. Pisco sour was excellent as well, possibly a little more pisco than most recopies.
Really tasty and fresh food

A MUST go!!!! Best ceviche I have had and all food and service incredible with amazing sea views- I would go back without a doubt. The prices are really reasonable compared to other good restaurants! If you love delicous food...you will love this place!!!
Great ceviche and tiradito! The octopus was absolutely amazing. The ceviche was tender and just acidic enough.
You can enjoy tasty sea food while looking the sea, a park and enjoying a talk with friends
I love the place my favourite Sunday afternoon retreat
The fish there has probably been frozen and defrosted. The ceviche there isn’t fresh and the sweet potatoes that came with it was canned. Do not go.

Without doubt this is probably the best buffet style restaurant that I’ve ever eaten in.  The quality and the vast offerings were amazing.  Then they bring out the weapons such as the eye fillet steak, salmon, chips with garlic and parsley as the entree, need I say more.

This is a must if you are visiting Buenos Aires. Top of the line all-you-can-eat cold cuts, excellent meats. We sat outside on the grass overlooking the sea. Waiters are top notch. Prices are around U$S 30 each, which is super low for us visitors.
 As a native Argentinean myself, I know abut Argentinean meat and restaurants. Do not pay attention to locals complaining about prices. Maybe this is not the place for them and some locals love to argue and complain. 
I was at Rodizio Costanera 3 days in a row!!.
I will-of course-be back when I return to Buenos Aires.
Excellent service, awesome meat, and a wonderful river view.
Tofo ok
It has a nice view, fair prices, but do not go to their bathroom
Really good food! the only thing that could have been better is the attendence.

Main dishes are based on fish, however they also offer other dishes based on meat. Good appetizers and deserts to wrap it all up. Prices reasonable. On Sunday they open up at 1200 pm. Gets crowded promptly.  Valet parking service available.
Great seafood. Peruviam style. Great service. Sensible prices. Food presentation and taste is great. Casual place good for small or large groups.
Nice place, good food but way too much people and can't have a normal conversation
Ok

Great service and food. Little bit pricey.

Great historic value & enjoyed the the info Its not very busy & You will not be there long as it's quite small Worth checking out if your looking for something to do Easy walk to get there !!!
Very interesting place!!! Amazing view from the top!!!! Totally worth the visit
This is a great reconstruction of the pyramid. They accept US cash and no credit or debit cards. Great view at the top.
There's no much to see. Only one pyramid without murals or any other ornament. I felt disappointed :(

I was a bit disappointed to find out they basically reconstructed the whole thing. The museum was under maintenance construction when I visited, and the temporary one was only very small. However, the view of the surrounding city on top of the pyramid is quite surreal.

This place is interesting and amazing! You can go with your family and friends. I'm sure you'll spend a really good time with them. Also, you can eat there or maybe prepare your own food and go with it , don't forget see and take photos to the beautiful animals.

Good family fun in a big zoo, better than I expected and my toddler really enjoyed seeing some of his favorite animals, like zebras, a giraffe, and a great variety of monkeys. Animals seem to be healthy and well fed (although an enclosed space will never be ideal for any of them). I hear it can get very crowded on the weekends, but we went at 9 am on a week day and it was almost empty the first 3 hours. It can get very hot in the summer, and there is very little shade, so prepare accordingly.

Great zoo overall - built right on top of some ancient ruins and plenty to do and see. We spent 4 hours there and we could have easily spent 4 more. Good place for a family picnic; we went on a Saturday and only the Amazon area was really too crowded with people.

It was an overall aesthetically pleasing zoo with a variety of animals but they lack care for the animals. Around 90% of the animals are sleeping and hiding while locked up in their four walls... You do not get much of an experience from seeing this. Also it was saddening to see how skinny some animals were such as the tiger they had. I've never seen one so skinny at a park before. Wouldn't come here again.
The best in the world! Excellent view of the different animals from the different regions of Peru

Good ceviche and seafood, good find if you look for something in the area.

The restaurant is a bit noisy.

I had a good lunch her during a weekday with some business colleagues. I had a ceviche dish with some fried calamari and some stacked potato-like thing. We shared an appetizer -- something like wontons. We drank some green lemonade. Had picarones for dessert. All good. Good service. Good prices.
Good place
Nice ceviches
The best ceviche ever. Very professional and attentive staff.

One of the best sushi places in Lima. They have really nice Peruvian fusion sushis. Fish is fresh. The Peruvian tuna is to die for! I would have eaten a lot more if I had the space. Place fills up very fast over the weekend so best to early.
Great food! Very unique mix of Japanese and Peruvian cusines. Fast and good service and affordable price.
Great sushi place. Sushi was fresh and tasty. Be prepared to wait in line, but it's worth it.

Great sushi in a casual but refined setting. They have many of the classics but also they have different unique Peruvian twists. Good example of Peruvian adaptations to other cuisines. Prices are more than other types of food in Peru, but in reality it's still a more than fair price. The juices are also fresh and tasty!

I don’t eat seafood and I was so happy to see they had these 2 amazingly delicious options for me! (Eggplant and chicken rolls) My husband was thrilled with his order too. We will surly be going back! Soooooo good!
Excellent sea and shrink food
Excellent ceviche, excellent service
Delicious fishing food...!!!
Nice sea food without being as expensive as other places. It is not cheap but serving sizes are more than adequate.
Because they took a lot time to bring the food and it was crowded.

Excelente

Muy bueno como siempre. Recomendado

Location is very good, near the seaside and walking distance to shopping Centre and Indian market. Breakfast is good but the AC is not working in my room. Since it is spring it's OK  I just open the window. They offer a fan for you if you want. Room is not big but good enough for 2 person. Breakfast is decent with a egg station which we don't find in  hotels in Brazil and Argentina.
Very good. Clean and good staff
Nice location. Decent room. Good breakfast by Peru vian standards.
Very good hotel. Only down side is that Sony have a gym.
My room was noisy, no air, no heat, no tissue.  The receptionist seems hate everybody.  Other than that, the location is great which makes up a lots of shortcomings.

You’ll always find a good art exhibit here. I have visited many times and it never disappoints. One of my favorite exhibits was of neon posters also called “afiches chicha” and the best part is that I got to take one with me with the info about the exhibit. I was in Peru a couple of weeks ago, and we were able to see their most recent one with interesting interactive and multimedia elements.
Great
Art is eternal
A quaint art gallery with plenty of temporary art exhibits.  Hit and miss, but you can usually find something interesting (for free) to check out!
Siento que podría brindar una mejor experiencia. Fuera de eso, buen espacio, buenas exposiciones y buenos recorridos guiados.

Service and food, from appetizer to dessert was as good as you can get... Outstanding resteraunt in outstanding location. My highest recommendation... You will not be disappointed but you will pay a reasonable amount for this excellent experience

All in all, what you see from the outside is what you get. As Canadians visiting in February, we made the grave error of visiting during the heat of the day. This place is a hot hellscape on a Peruvian summer day. Only accessible during a tour, the location offers no respite from the sun. The tour takes a full hour, which, while very interesting and educational, is a bit of a long time to be looking at bricks. Our tour guide was very good, and we enjoyed learning about Lima culture, but there isn't much to see other than the clay mud bricks and the views from the top, which are definitely quite good. If you plan to visit, go during the evening.

It you like the exploring of archeology and history  this place will be great for you. Free guided tour. But I would have preferred to wander alone (sign are all there at points of interest)
Love to see what it looks like at night as it now has night tours

Great place to learn about and see ancient ruins. They even have two Peruvian Hairless Dogs "guarding" the pyramid. This site is huge and the preservation does a great job to recreate the life that existed in this area.

Very interesting piece of history. Guided tours are mandatory and price of entrance is beyond reasonable. Day tours take you up the pyramid while night tours do not. You'll spend about 1.5 hours max if only going to the ruins. Something nice to do if you are in Lima.
Upscale place, they have Peruvian specialties based on fish with a Japanese twist. Good ceviche and shrimp tempura. Outstanding service.

Fancy place to eat.  Very good food and variety.  You are paying here for the quality you are getting.  If you can afford $$$ places like this one, don't miss the chance to taste the good dishes prepared hete.
Lovely place, excellent food and service. Great atmosphere
Excellent, great service. Food is wonderful, i loved fish in salt foil.
Salted Chita is Amazing so if you go that is what you have to order. Best fish ever

One of the best sushi places in Lima. They have really nice Peruvian fusion sushis. Fish is fresh. The Peruvian tuna is to die for! I would have eaten a lot more if I had the space. Place fills up very fast over the weekend so best to early.
Great food! Very unique mix of Japanese and Peruvian cusines. Fast and good service and affordable price.
Great sushi place. Sushi was fresh and tasty. Be prepared to wait in line, but it's worth it.

Great sushi in a casual but refined setting. They have many of the classics but also they have different unique Peruvian twists. Good example of Peruvian adaptations to other cuisines. Prices are more than other types of food in Peru, but in reality it's still a more than fair price. The juices are also fresh and tasty!

I don’t eat seafood and I was so happy to see they had these 2 amazingly delicious options for me! (Eggplant and chicken rolls) My husband was thrilled with his order too. We will surly be going back! Soooooo good!
The best food in Lima so far. This restaurant definitely worth the experience. Excellent cousin, service was perfect. Every dish is better than another.

Sensational restaurant!  All around fantastic.  Service, atmosphere, food, location.  Everything is always superb!  A cozy luncheon or dinner in the bar is my favorite.  Great menu variety and wonderful wines.
Amazing quality and service. Well worth it. Came to Lima for a break and a late celebration of my birthday. Very happy with everything!

We were a party of 3 and we ordered a real feast here. We'd just returned from a hike in the sacred valley that day so all we had were casual jeans and hiking fleeces - they didn't seem to mind so the dress code is not so formal. The restaurant does serve fine dining food though. We had the lamb brains (creamy and divine), scallops (fresh and tasty but a little small), 2 fish mains (really good) and a pasta dish (just OK). It's expensive for Peruvian standards but the service, fresh produce, originality of the dishes and flavours made it worthwhile. Very popular with the locals too. It was packed when we were there so do make reservations.
Amazing food and service

Love this place! It's huge, with restaurant and several bars. We went to one of the bars. Excellent cocktails and food! Service outstanding, attentive, they went out of their way to make us feel comfortable.
Really good restaurant where you can taste the typical Peruvian food.  The buffet has a wide variety.  Prices are reasonable and quality is excellent.
Good ambiance but that's about it. Service was ok, food nothing special, fish wasn't fresh, drink was weak. Wouldn't go back.

Best lunch buffet in Lima! The style is comida criolla (i.e. coastal, excluding seafood).Not cheap but good value given the huge variety, quality and service. Located in a classic Miraflores manor, everything is delicious and prepared the classic way. Go hungry!
One of the best places in Lima!!! Memorable service,  incredible food, great location!   5/5 stars all around!!!
Great sandwiches, a bit pricy but great service and clean safe spot.

Pricey enough but an absolutely delicious sandwich. I got the 'chicharon', a delicious pork sandwich. I'd recommend getting the french fries too to make sure you're full after the meal. 10/10 on the service too, lovely woman working behind the counter who served us :)
A great store for sandwiches. We tried the lechon a la Lena. The pork was moist and flavoursome and the bread was super fluffy and fresh. Staff were excellent too.
Awhhhhh just mouth watering to think about, such good food and the price is pretty reasonable for what you get. If your looking for quality for la lucha is unreal
This place isn't cheap but they make tasty sandwiches. The chicharron is the way to go here. The combination of pork and sweet potato is so delicious. Definitely worth a stop for a quick bite.
It's very small but very varied on the bubble tea drinks they offer along with Japanese treats. Loved it. Worth every sol spent.
The name says everything, an small shop with great buble teas, ask for olong tea with taro and a min pao
Best bubble tea in the whole city
Best bubble teas in lima
Nice place. Try assam tea.

Absolutely fantastic! I sat on the terrace underneath a gorgeous flowering tree. The waiters are extremely attentive and knowledgeable of the menu. The food is well prepared, flavored excellently, and presented fantastically.  I recommend ordering the banana creme brûlée for dessert with chocolate truffles - to die for!

Love the fusion there! Turns out the fish we ordered  was cooked in Thai style which I love the most. Very casual and relaxing atmosphere and the waiter there was welcoming. Each main course is around 50 soles or so.
Stop reading, just go!  Great food. Very reasonably priced.  Fun location.
Awesome, awesome food. We’re been traveling for about a month and this place had the best food yet
Probably one of the best meals we had in Lima. Highly recommended!

Fantastic rooms, great views. Hotel service was slow and food in the restaurant wasn't as good as I'd hoped. In fairness, the staff were very nice and helpful but because of the hotel's layout, getting to the rooms isn't fast or easy.

Excellent choice, the hotel is amazing, something truly different. You can get a private pool right on your room with an amazing view, the jeep ride to get in and out of the hotel is something nice too. Definitely staying here again.

visited hundreds of hotels during my private and business time in over 115 countries, lot of beaches but I have to say this hotel is in my TOP5. Private pool in 2floor room, super clean, hidden from people, private balcony with best view on Acapulco bay, window for food and drinks for keeping your privacy and extraordinary service. Food was excellent. I literally spend two full days just in room enjoying privacy, view and my spacious pool and private terrace. Will return no doubt! :)

Very interesting concept, some flows in it tho. I love the idea of privacy (had a room with private pool). Stayed Wednesday through Sunday.  Unfortunately, on Friday-Saturday the place got crowded. Loud noises, different music playing from  four different places, loud laughter, kids screaming, etc. 
They say Breakfast included, but in fact it's a pot of coffee ans two small pastries, all other food you have to order/ go to one of the restaurants. Speaking of ordering - room service is extremely quick and professional. 
Beach Club is nice - salt water pool is so much fun. Fish ans sea stars are everywhere!
Sunset Bar is another cool place - you can enjoy the sunset from the top of the mountain having a drink.
Overall, I'd say i enjoyed my stay there.

Aging property with beautiful views. The rooms are definitely dated but not a huge deal to me. The beach club is a highlight but the shuttle to get to and from the beach club takes way too long. It's about a 10 minute ride from the beach club to the hotel but we'd wait sometimes 45 minutes for a ride.
